  "body": "### Description\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: Send transaction should not redirect to public chat where \"send\" command is not available. Instead, it should redirect to 1-1 chat.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nClicking send transaction button in profile screen opened from public chat should redirect to 1-1 chat.  \r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nIt redirects back to the public chat where \"send\" command is not available. \r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n- Click on a profile in a public chat\r\n- Click Send transaction\r\nYou are now in the public chat with \"/send\" in input, but this command is not available in public chats. It maybe makes sense in case of a group chat. But, to make it simple I'd always redirect to 1-1 chat if \"Send transaction\" is clicked in a profile screen.\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: #3547\r\n* Operating System: Android, iOS",
